  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Secure Email - Edit Transactions</title>

    <para role="TEXT">This option is used to complete a Secure Email
    notification that a user has already started and saved, to be
    completed.<indexterm>
        <primary>Retrieve</primary>

        <secondary>Secure Email Draft</secondary>
      </indexterm><indexterm>
        <primary>Secure Email</primary>

        <secondary>Edit Transactions</secondary>
      </indexterm><indexterm>
        <primary>Edit Transactions</primary>

        <secondary>Secure Email</secondary>
      </indexterm></para>

    <para role="TEXT">When this option is selected, a list is displayed of
    Secure Email notifications that have been prepared and saved by users in
    the bank, but not yet submitted to the clients because the input user
    either did not try to submit or had insufficient privileges.</para>

    <para role="TEXT"><graphic fileref="./images/BUG_MidOff_secure_edit.jpg"
    width="160mm"/></para>

    <para role="TEXT">Click the <emphasis role="bold">Search
    Options</emphasis> link to display the fields that can be used to filter
    the list. Only complete the fields that are required for the filter. The
    columns in the resulting list show the <xi:include
    href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="System_ID"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>, Bank Ref, <xi:include
    href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="Entity"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/><emphasis role="bold">,
    Advices Type, Account Number, Topic, Input</emphasis> and <emphasis
    role="bold">Status</emphasis> of each message.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Click on the <emphasis role="bold"> <xi:include
    href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="System_ID"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/></emphasis> column of the
    required entry to open it for further editing.</para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Secure Email - Retrieve Unsigned</title>

    <para role="TEXT">This option is used by an authorised bank user, to
    submit a Secure Email notification that a bank user has already started
    but been unable to submit due to insufficient authority.<indexterm>
        <primary>Retrieve</primary>

        <secondary>Unsigned Secure Email</secondary>
      </indexterm><indexterm>
        <primary>Secure Email</primary>

        <secondary>Retrieve Unsigned</secondary>
      </indexterm><indexterm>
        <primary>Retrieve Unsigned</primary>

        <secondary>Secure Email</secondary>
      </indexterm></para>

    <para role="TEXT">When this option is selected, a list is displayed of
    Secure Email notifications that have been prepared and saved by users in
    the bank, but have not been successfully submitted to the clients because
    the user had insufficient privileges. Records that were simply saved with
    no attempt to submit them are not included.</para>

    <para role="TEXT"><graphic
    fileref="./images/BUG_MidOff_secure_unsigned.jpg" width="160mm"/></para>

    <para role="TEXT">Click the <emphasis role="bold">Search
    Options</emphasis> link to display the fields that can be used to filter
    the list. Only complete the fields that are required for the
    filter.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">Click on the <emphasis role="bold"> <xi:include
    href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="System_ID"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/></emphasis> column of the
    required entry to open it in a non-editable mode, in order to review the
    data and perform the submission. If sufficient authorisations are
    allocated in the profile of the authorising user, multiple records can be
    submitted in a single operation directly from the list. Each record in the
    list has a check box which must be ticked to select it. A <emphasis
    role="bold">Submit</emphasis> button at the end of the page, submits all
    the selected records.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">The result of the action is then returned, with a list
    of records that have now been successfully sent to the clients, together
    with a list of records that have again failed validation. The updated list
    of unsigned records is re-displayed.</para>
  </section>
</section>
